commit.message: Switched to proper Python 3.8 in Travis config
Added version number
Updated Travis configuration to work with Python 3.7+
Added Travis configuration for Python 3.8
Updated python_requires to exclude Python 3.4

Added support for column comments

Closes #97. Closes #92.
Dropped support for SQLalchemy 0.8

Fixed crash on unrecognized column types

Fixes #72.

Dropped support for Python 3.4 and added support for 3.7 and 3.8

Also added official support for SQLAlchemy 1.3.
Added note about the latest PR to CHANGES

Import vendor-specific types when generic types cannot be used. (#75)

* Import vendor-specific types when generic types cannot be used.

If a vendor-specific type cannot be adapted to a generic sqlalchemy then
import the vendor-specific type rather than the generic type. Some
vendor-specific types have different constructors. E.g., MySQL INTEGER,
which takes an optional display width.

* Bugfix for mysql TINYTEXT, MEDIUMTEXT, and LONGTEXT.

Don't adapt types further if they cannot be compiled.

Fixes #67.
Skipped another test that gives inconsistent results on SQLA < 1.0

Fixed secondary= not taking into account the association table's schema

Fixes #30.

Skip an occasionally failing test on SQLAlchemy < 1.0

The class ordering appears to change based on the random hash there.
Fixed tests broken by the previous commit

Use built-in table sort order instead of sorting by schema and name

Fixes #15, fixes #16.

Fixed quoting of server defaults which themselves contain double quotes

Fixes #7, fixes #17, fixes #28, fixes #33, fixes #36.

Changed single character alternation to a class expression in a regex

PyCharm was complaining about this.
Properly test dialect specific column types with appropriate engines
